KPI Sheet 3 (Avg Order Price) 13



1. Right click on Total Sales worksheet and select Duplicate. Rename the new sheet as Avg Order Price.


2. Remove all the values from Marks card. Drag and drop Avg Order Price, Quantity, Avg Price MoM, Avg Price KPI Indicator Down, Avg Price KPI Indicator UP to Text under Marks card.

3. Select <AGG(Avg Order Price)>. Font = Tableau Bold, Size = 16, Alignment = Center, Color = #000000

4.Arrange <AGG(Avg Price MoM %)> <AGG(Avg Price KPI Indicator Down)> <AGG(Avg Price KPI Indicator UP)> in the same line. 

Select <AGG(Avg Price MoM %)> <AGG(Avg Price KPI Indicator Down)> <AGG(Avg Price KPI Indicator UP)>. Font = Tableau Medium, Bold, Alignment Center. 

<AGG(Avg Price MoM %)> Size = 10, Color = #009867,

<AGG(Avg Price KPI Indicator Down)> Size=12, Color = #aa0000,

<AGG(Avg Price KPI Indicator Up)> Size=12, Color = #005500

Click OK.

5. Click on Text and Alignment. Select Center alignment for both Horizontal and Verticle.

6. Click on Tooltip under Marks and enter the following text:

Avg Order Price: <AGG(Avg Order Price)>

 Avg Price MoM: <AGG(Avg Price MoM %)>

Font = Tableau Book, Size = 10, Alignment = Left

Avg Order Price, Avg Price MoM – Color = #787878

<AGG(Avg Price MoM%)>, <AGG(Avg Order Price)> - Color = #333333

7. Drag and drop Date Filter to Filters shelf and select only True option.

8. Click on Title, Edit Title. Enter the text Avg Order Price.
